        "title": "Move cron persistence to SQLite",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Move cron jobs, runtime state, and run history from legacy JSON/JSONL files into the shared OpenClaw state SQLite database.\n- Import valid legacy cron stores/logs on first read and archive legacy files only after durable SQLite import; malformed legacy stores stay on disk until quarantine succeeds.\n- Preserve `stateOnly` runtime updates without replacing concurrent cron config edits, and harden early SQLite cron tables with additive column repair.\n- Update cron/task/docs/config wording and focused regression coverage for legacy import, quarantine, run logs, early rows, and state schema upgrades.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core:test`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/state/openclaw-state-db.test.ts src/cron/store.test.ts src/cron/run-log.test.ts src/cron/run-log.error-reason.test.ts src/cron/service.store-load-invalid-main-job.test.ts src/cron/service/store.load-missing-session-target.test.ts src/cron/service/store.test.ts src/cron/service.persists-delivered-status.test.ts src/commands/doctor-cron.test.ts src/commands/doctor-cron-store-migration.test.ts src/commands/tasks.test.ts src/tasks/task-registry.maintenance.issue-60299.test.ts`\n- `pnpm config:docs:check`\n- `git diff --check`\n- autoreview: clean for branch after fixes\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Cron jobs, runtime state, and run logs migrate to shared SQLite while preserving malformed legacy rows for quarantine and preserving runtime-only state updates.\n\nReal environment tested: Local macOS focused tests; Blacksmith Testbox was attempted twice.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: The commands listed in Verification were run after the final patch. `pnpm check:changed` was attempted via Testbox IDs `tbx_01ksvyx2a3hg6h59skrf701b8w` and `tbx_01ksw3frxw7zn0cmbgqxpdqr28`.\n\nEvidence after fix: Focused cron/state/task/docs/type checks passed locally. Autoreview had no accepted/actionable findings for this branch.\n\nObserved result after fix: Legacy cron stores import/archive into SQLite, malformed legacy rows remain available until quarantine, state-only saves update runtime columns without deleting/reinserting config rows, and early cron SQLite schemas are additively repaired.\n\nWhat was not tested: Full `pnpm check:changed` did not complete because both Blacksmith Testbox attempts were cancelled/stalled by infra before producing code-failure output.\n",
